Description

Offering views of Rovinj Old Town, the nearby islands and Adriatic Sea, Grand Park Hotel features a wellness and spa center, outdoor swimming pool and a private marina. The hotel features various restaurants, bars and a pastry shop. The buffet breakfast is served daily in the main hotel restaurant. The wellness area offers different types of saunas, steam rooms and indoor pools. Guests can enjoy various activities, such as tennis, jogging and cycling.

Facilities

indoor and outdoor pool / Fitness center / Spa / Massages / Sauna / Hammam / Lift / Air condition

420 Sqf, balcony, bath, connecting room, twin bed, walkin shower, electric kettle, coffee maker, flat screen TV

Yacht description

Staff: Captain, sailor and maid
Cabins: Master cabin, 2 cabins (one with twin beds) all with en suite bathroom
Leonidas amenities: 2 bottles of champaigne and plate of canapes upon arrival

The AZIMUT 66 FLYBRIDGE is a luxurious and sophisticated express cruiser that delivers good performance and luxury accommodations. The yacht features a spacious cockpit for entertaining and sunbathing and offers five private staterooms below. It includes three guest cabins with double beds, one twin cabin and one crew cabin with two separate beds.

Specifications: Overall length: 20,08 m (68' 24''ft) / Beam: 5.23 m / Draft: 1,6 m / Engines: 2 x 1150 mHP 847 (kW) CAT C18 ACERT / Cruise speed: 28 knots
Notes: here will be displayed yacht notes
Inclusions: approx. 5h
Exclusions: approx. 5h

Azimuth 66 provides spacious seating and sunbathing areas, including a large sun pad and lounge areaup on the bow. Spacious teak deck features a dining table for six and a separate lounge area. In caseof bad weather there is a big lounge area and a dinning table in the lower deck, that gives you only aglimpse of the luxury this cruiser boasts. The available entertainment center and tastefully decorated interior, combined with a fully-equippedgalley give the yacht an at home, comfortable feel the guests can enjoy while cruising the beautifulAdriatic and visiting some of the most beautiful islands. At the helm, the innovative Optimus Electronic Power Steering system by Seastar Solutions gives youa similar sensation to driving a top of the range car. The owner can configure the responsiveness ofthe helm by regulating wheel turns and steering effort according to speed. The system also has theadditional benefi t of eliminating the hydraulic piping between the helm station and the ruddercompartment.

05

Saturday @ 10:00

Gatro tour

Private excursion to Gorska Brda and Nova Gorica with cooking class

Goriska brda and Nova Gorica with cooking class

Meeting point: hotel lobby @ 10:00
Duration: approx. 5h

Join your guide for a private cooking class and sightseeing tour in one of the most recognizable and strongest wine regions in Slovenia, Goriska Brda. While cooking, you will discover how this region has evolved over time and how people of this area live today. You will return to the time of our grandfathers and grandmothers and rediscover the dishes from those times, get to know the local recipes and learn some new things about olive oil, local producers and of course you are going to taste some. After sightseeing of Goriska Brda, this tour will take you to one of the youngest Slovenian cities, Nova Gorica. Enjoy sightseeing and listen to the interesting story of the life in the Nova Gorica.

Inclusions: private guide, round transfers, cooking class
Exclusions: tickets, gratuities and items purchased for personal use

Hvar's nightlife

Hvar's nightlife

Notes: here will be displayed several notes about this description

The sunny island of Hvar, as its nicknamed, is another hyped party destination on the Croatian coast. Historically, Hvar has always attracted the rich and famous. The popularity of this island among the young has increased over the past few years due to all the great bars and summer clubs. Clubs like Carpe Diem, Hula Hula Hvar, Pink Champagne arent short of summer thrills and youll soon realize youve found yourself in some of the best bars and clubs on this side of the Adriatic. The downside is the price. Hvar is very upmarket so if youre short on budget, youll be better off on Pags Zrce beach. Summer night life in town Hvar is one of the richest on the Adriatic. The town has a special flair and there is always something going on. Parties last all night long and guests can visit numerous events, restaurants, taverns, pubs, clubs etc.
